/scratch/gilbreth/li5042/transkun/transkun_fork/transkun/computeMetrics.py:192: FutureWarning: As of SciPy 1.17, users must choose a p-value calculation method by providing the `method` parameter. `method='interpolate'` interpolates the p-value from pre-calculated tables; `method` may also be an instance of `MonteCarloMethod` to approximate the p-value via Monte Carlo simulation. When `method` is specified, the result object will include a `pvalue` attribute and not attributes `critical_value`, `significance_level`, or `fit_result`. Beginning in 1.19.0, these other attributes will no longer be available, and a p-value will always be computed according to one of the available `method` options.
